{"key":"post-16390433","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16390433</id>\n<content>If you're using agar-agar from an oriental store, you need to mix it into the recommended amount of water and bring it to a rapid boil.&amp;nbsp; It won't dissolve until then.&amp;nbsp; Don't forget, you also have to add malt as a nutrient source.&amp;nbsp; The agar-agar is just the gelling agent.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you're using lab grade MEA such as fungi.com sells, you can mix it into cold water, shake well and sterilize.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16390456</next>\n<prev>16390425</prev>\n<first>16390425</first>\n<last>16393720</last>\n<when>1339879147</when>\n<utime>06/16/12 11:39 PM</utime>\n</post>"}